Preconditions:
- The input `n` must be an integer greater than or equal to - The input `cuts` must be an array of integers with a length greater than or equal to - Each element in the `cuts` array must be an integer between 1 and `n-1`.
- All elements in the `cuts` array must be distinct.

Postconditions:
- The method should return an integer representing the minimum total cost of the cuts.
- The order of the cuts can be changed.
- The cost of one cut is the length of the stick to be cut.
- When a stick is cut, it will be split into two smaller sticks, and the sum of their lengths will be equal to the length of the stick before the cut.